-- Philip Morris Says Czech Market Fell 3.5% in Third Quarter
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-10-18T13:35:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-18/philip-morris-says-czech-market-fell-3-5-in-third-quarter.html
Philip Morris International Inc. (PM) ,
the world’s largest publicly traded tobacco company, said the
total cigarette market in the Czech Republic fell 3.5 percent in
the third quarter.  Czech market share for the company’s brands fell 2
percentage points to 42.5 percent during the three months
period, the cigarette maker said in a regulatory statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
